Amalgamated Appliance, Argent, Telkom: S. Africa Stock Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-06-06T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/amalgamated-appliance-argent-telkom-s-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index gained 2.38, or less
than 0.1 percent, to 31,578.03 in Johannesburg.  Amalgamated Appliance Holdings Ltd. (AMA SJ): The maker of
ceramic tiles and sanitary equipment said it has entered into
talks which, if successfully concluded, may have a material
effect on its share price. The shares dropped 1 cent, or 0.6
percent, to 1.79 rand.  Argent Industrial Ltd. (ART)  : The investment holding
company said earnings per share rose as much as 375 percent in
the year ended March 31. The company reports earnings on 23
June. The shares were unchanged at 8.40 rand.  Business Connexion Group Ltd. (BCX)  : The information
technology provider said it agreed to buy a controlling stake in
Dusty Moon Investments 333 (Pty) Ltd., a printing services
business, for 240 million rand ($35 million). Business
Connexion’s shares were unchanged on 4.90 rand.  Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TKG SJ): Africa’s biggest fixed-
line operator expects judgment on civil action its Multi-Links
Telecommunications Ltd. unit initiated against Helios Investment
Partners LLP about the validity of a lease agreement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: 
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  